    "en": {
      "title": "Temporary permission for Adani to build two thermal power plants",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Power and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said today (16) that India's Adani company has been given temporary approval to develop two wind power plant projects in Mannar and Punarin and the investment will exceed 500 million US dollars.",
        "The Minister further said that 286 megawatts will be generated from the Mannar Power Plant and 234 megawatts from the Punareen Basin.",
        "This decision was reached during the discussion held today (16) with CEB and Sustainable Development Authority officials to discuss the progress of renewable energy projects."
      ],
